    "name": "Per Dunsö",
    "profile": "Swedish actor, musician and composer, born June 23, 1949 in Ronneby.\r\n\r\nDunsö grew up in Ronneby and moved with the family to Malmö in the early 1960s. During his high school years, he worked as a ticket caretaker at Malmö City Theater. For the money he earned at the theater, he bought his first guitar. At the city theater, he also came in contact with director Ronny Danielsson and got the chance to compose music for a number of children's theater performances. He also got to participate as an actor in the cabaret Plutbröst 1976; Ingalill Persson (a member of the mixed group Mixed media) also participated in the same performance, which he later married. The collaboration with Ronny Danielsson continued with children's radio programs, including the series \"Doktor Kling och syster Violina\".\r\n\r\nIn 1974 he released his own solo album Dit vingarna bär.\r\n\r\nDunsö studied musicology in Lund 1971–1972 and there he got to know the musician Ola Ström. The collaboration between Dunsö and Ström beg",
